hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I'm sorry, he's generic for mobic medication Alongside Simon Russell Beale as the outrageously camp drag artist in a British Army song-and-dance unit in Malaya in 1948, Haque played the troupe's sole female, enduring racial prejudice while instructing the virginal Private Steven Flowers (Joseph Timms) in the art of love. During her short run in the play, she complained of severe backache and abdominal pain. After the production's Christmas break she was admitted to hospital and died in her sleep after having breathing problems. Doctors believed the cause to be cancer.
